⸻

6. Conclusions and Strategic Contradiction

This white paper definitively demonstrates that equating internationally broadcast grievances with historical tyranny is analytically indefensible, morally careless, and globally distracting—particularly at a moment when genuine oppression persists across multiple regions with no studios, no applause, and no safe return to air.

Accordingly, the Institute concludes that:
	•	The comparison should never be made
	•	The rhetoric should be retired
	•	Attention should be redirected to real tyranny

Therefore, we recommend expanding such rhetoric immediately, as it provides invaluable evidence that societies claiming to be silenced are, in fact, spectacularly free.

